            <thetext>Whenever a user enters a very long word which forces scrollbars to show the cursor is not moved to the current location. Instead the typed text is shown and the cursor is not moving with the text. Also the scrollbar is growing.

If the user clicks at any other location of the text which is *not* within the normal range (the part of the editor which is visible without scrollbars) the text is entered at this position, but the cursor is still not moving.

This issue is reported at bugzilla.webkit under https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=33209.</thetext>
